						<div class="postbody"><div class="quotetitle">Canite wrote:</div><div class="quotecontent">So, does the CPU "fall through" to the next line at all times, until it's told to jump somewhere else, where it will begin to fall through from there?</div><br />Yes. Without a jump, the program counter will just keep counting.<br /><br /><div class="quotetitle"><b>Quote:</b></div><div class="quotecontent">What happens when the CPU gets to the end of the code?</div>
<br />The program counter will count into data in the ROM that isn't intended as a program, and the instruction decoder will start interpreting it as garbage instructions. And about 5% of garbage instructions will hang a 6502 CPU.</div>

